    <h2>Dough Sheeter Width Sizes — Which One Do You Need?</h2>

    <p>The belt or roller width of a dough sheeter machine determines the maximum width of dough sheet it can produce. Choosing the right width is crucial — too narrow and you will be making multiple passes for wide products; too wide and you are paying for capacity you do not use.</p>

