    <h2>Dough Sheeter Machine — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What is the price of a dough sheeter machine in India?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Dough sheeter machine prices in India in 2026 start from approximately ₹45,000 for a basic table-top 450mm model from an Indian brand and go up to ₹12,00,000 or more for a premium European floor-standing reversible sheeter. The most popular range for small to medium Indian bakeries is ₹80,000 to ₹3,00,000, which covers imported table-top and floor-standing non-reversible models from brands like Sinmag and Berjaya.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Which is the best dough sheeter brand in India?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">For most Indian bakeries, Sinmag (Taiwan) offers the best balance of quality, reliability, and price. For premium operations and serious croissant/puff pastry production, Ferneto (Portugal) and Rondo (Switzerland) are the top choices. Among Indian brands, Ekon and Spar offer acceptable quality for basic sheeting applications at budget-friendly prices.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Do I need a reversible or non-reversible dough sheeter?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">If you make laminated doughs (croissants, puff pastry, Danish pastries), a reversible sheeter is strongly recommended — it saves significant time and operator effort by automatically reversing the dough direction between passes. For simpler applications like pizza bases, roti, paratha, or cookies, a non-reversible sheeter is perfectly adequate and much more affordable.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What size dough sheeter do I need for a small bakery?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">For a small bakery producing up to 50 kg of dough per day, a table-top dough sheeter with a 450mm or 500mm belt width is usually sufficient. This covers most applications including small pizza bases, pastry, and flatbreads. If you plan to grow, consider investing in a 520mm model for added versatility.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Can I use a dough sheeter for making roti and chapati?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Yes, a dough sheeter machine can roll out roti and chapati dough to uniform thickness very quickly. However, for very high-volume roti production (hundreds per hour), a dedicated roti making machine is more efficient as it both rolls and shapes the dough into rounds. A sheeter is ideal when you need to make both flatbreads and pastry products on the same machine.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How much electricity does a dough sheeter consume?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">A table-top dough sheeter with a 0.25–0.5 HP motor consumes approximately 0.2–0.4 kWh per hour of operation. A floor-standing reversible model with a 1–2 HP motor consumes 0.75–1.5 kWh per hour. In terms of monthly electricity cost, a typical small bakery using a table-top sheeter for 2–3 hours daily would spend approximately ₹300–₹600 per month on sheeter electricity at standard commercial rates.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How long does a dough sheeter machine last?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">With proper maintenance, a quality dough sheeter machine lasts 10–15 years or more. European brands like Rondo and Ferneto are known for exceptional longevity. The conveyor belt is the primary consumable — expect to replace it every 1–3 years depending on usage intensity, at a cost of ₹5,000–₹25,000 depending on the machine model. The motor, rollers, and frame should last the lifetime of the machine with proper care.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Where can I buy a dough sheeter machine in India?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Dough sheeters are available from bakery equipment dealers in major cities including Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Kolkata, and Pune. You can also purchase through online B2B platforms like IndiaMART and TradeIndia, though we recommend buying from authorised brand dealers for warranty protection and after-sales service. Check our guide on <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-suppliers-india">bakery equipment suppliers in India</a> for verified dealer recommendations in your city.</div>
